Edition:
Quote: Dissatisfied younger sons, ambitious women or slighted elders sought redress by force of arms or went into [72] the open spaces of Aotearoa or Tewaipounamu. Our Courts recognised the arikiship in the award of shares in land ...
Notes: Ngata, 1933 in 1988
